

# Thoughts gathering

## Single file component
<template></template>
<script></script>
<style></style>


Config:
  - site: default site config 
  - env: environment specific site config
  - build: build Config
  - serve: config for serve, include livereload options
  - globals: globals config, include site layout etc

Global variables:
  site: site config
  data: data in /data folder
  __kolibri: kolibri info

Page variable: 
  page: data in the front matter
  this: alias to 'page'


### Build env

Run `kolibri build`, or to specify an env, use `kolibri build --env prod`

under config 'build.env', you can also specify the 'env'

If you want to bypass the env, you can either leave `build.env` as empty.

Same concept for 'serve'

# In pages

New variable 'this', along with 'page', "this" can be used "{{ page.title }} -> {{ this.title }}" 

